The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Referrals
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Referrals
                      
	Day III of the third Test saw six referrals being made. The referrals were:         
	 Anil Kumble challenged Rudi Koertzens decision of not ruling Ajantha Mendis out caught behind off Zaheer Khan. The TV umpire ruled in the batsmans favour.         
	 Sri Lanka asked for a review of Koertzens decision of not ruling Sourav Ganguly out off Mendis. The third umpire upheld the on-field umpires decision.         
	 Sourav asked for a review of Mark Bensons decision ruling him out off Muttiah Muralidharan. The TV umpire upheld the on-field umpires decision.         
	 Sri Lanka asked for a review of Bensons decision of not ruling Sachin Tendulkar out off Murali. The TV umpire upheld the on-field umpires decision.         
	 Sri Lanka asked for a review of Bensons decision of not ruling Tendulkar out off Murali. The TV umpire upheld the on-field umpires decision.         
	 Sachin Tendulkar asked for a review of Koertzens decision ruling him out lbw off Mendis. The TV umpire upheld the on-field umpires decision.                                                                                                                          
